  "text": "The Grafana unified alerting system evaluates alert rules and fires notifications through the following execution flow:\n\n## Rule Scheduling and Evaluation\n\nThe rule scheduler starts in `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go`. The `Run()` method (line 175) initializes a ticker and calls `schedulePeriodic()`, which continuously processes ticks. On each tick, `processTick()` (line 276) fetches alert rules from the database and determines which rules are ready to be evaluated. For each ready rule, it schedules an evaluation by calling `ruleRoutine.Eval()` on the corresponding alert rule routine.\n\nEach alert rule has its own goroutine running `alertRule.Run()` (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go, line 245). This event loop waits for evaluation signals on the `evalCh` channel. When an evaluation is triggered, it executes `alertRule.evaluate()` (line 392), which:\n\n1. Creates an evaluator using the evaluator factory\n2. Calls `ruleEval.Evaluate(ctx, e.scheduledAt)` (pkg/services/ngalert/eval/eval.go, line 410) to execute the rule's queries and expressions\n3. Returns evaluation results that indicate which alert instances should fire\n\n## State Transition and Determination\n\nAfter evaluation, the results are passed to the state manager's `ProcessEvalResults()` (pkg/services/ngalert/state/manager.go, line 313), which:\n\n1. Calls `setNextStateForRule()` (line 357) to determine the next state for each alert instance based on the evaluation results\n2. Processes missing series states (line 359) to handle resolved alerts\n3. Calls `updateLastSentAt()` (line 371) to determine which state transitions need to be sent to receivers\n4. Persists the state changes to the database\n5. Invokes an optional `send` callback with the `StateTransitions` that need to be delivered\n\nEach `StateTransition` (pkg/services/ngalert/state/state.go, line 289) represents a change in alert state. The `NeedsSending()` method (line 593) determines if a state transition should be sent based on the last send time and resend delay configuration.\n\n## Notification Dispatch\n\nThe state transitions are sent to the `AlertsRouter.Send()` method (pkg/services/ngalert/sender/router.go, line 316), which routes alerts to:\n\n1. The local Grafana alertmanager via `alertmanager.PutAlerts()` (pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/alertmanager.go, line 442)\n2. External Alertmanager instances via `ExternalAlertmanager.SendAlerts()` (pkg/services/ngalert/sender/sender.go, line 209)\n\nThe `alertmanager.PutAlerts()` method converts the PostableAlerts format and passes them to the base GrafanaAlertmanager for routing to configured receivers based on the notification policy configuration.\n\n## Key Components\n\n- **Rule Scheduler** (schedule.go): Coordinates periodic evaluation of alert rules using a base interval and jitter\n- **Alert Rule Routine** (alert_rule.go): Manages the lifecycle of individual rule evaluation with retry logic\n- **Evaluator** (eval.go): Executes the rule's condition against datasources\n- **State Manager** (state/manager.go): Tracks alert instance states and determines transitions\n- **Alerts Router** (sender/router.go): Routes alerts to local and external alertmanagers\n- **Local Alertmanager** (notifier/alertmanager.go): Processes alerts through the notification policy and routes to receivers\n"
}

